## Step 2 — Generate design assets via OpenRouter nanobanana

Call the OpenRouter API with the nanobanana model. Write a self-contained script:

```python
# /// script
# requires-python = ">=3.11"
# dependencies = ["requests"]
# ///
import os, requests, json, sys

api_key   = os.environ["OPENROUTER_API_KEY"]
palette   = json.loads(sys.argv[1])   # hex list from Step 1
task_desc = sys.argv[2]               # design task description

system = (
    "You are a world-class graphic designer. "
    "Return only valid, self-contained SVG or CSS. No markdown fences, no prose."
)

user = f"""
Design task: {task_desc}

Colour palette (use ONLY these colours):
{chr(10).join(f"  {h}" for h in palette)}

Produce a complete, production-ready SVG illustration or CSS design system
(whichever is most appropriate for the task). Be creative. Be precise.
"""

resp = requests.post(
    "https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions",
    headers={
        "Authorization": f"Bearer {api_key}",
        "Content-Type":  "application/json",
        "HTTP-Referer":  "https://github.com/KUKARAF/full_yolo",
    },
    json={
        "model":    "nanobanana",
        "messages": [
            {"role": "system",  "content": system},
            {"role": "user",    "content": user},
        ],
    },
    timeout=120,
)
resp.raise_for_status()
print(resp.json()["choices"][0]["message"]["content"])
```

Save as `_graphic_gen.py`. Run with:
```bash
OPENROUTER_API_KEY="<key>" uv run _graphic_gen.py '<palette_json>' '<task_desc>'
```

