## Step 3 — Save outputs

- Save the primary output (SVG / CSS) to `design/<slug>.svg` or `design/<slug>.css`
- Save the palette to `design/<slug>-palette.json`
- Write a short `design/<slug>-notes.md` describing the design decisions

Clean up the temporary `_palette_fetch.py` and `_graphic_gen.py` scripts.

---

## Rules

- Never hard-code colours — always pull from the fetched palette
- If the OpenRouter call fails, log the HTTP status and body, then exit with a non-zero code
- Prefer SVG for illustrations; CSS custom properties for design systems
- Commit all files under `design/` with a descriptive message
